Fable and Fable: The Lost Chapters

The first Fable was awesome. The story line was awesome. And not only did Jack of Blades (final boss) die once, but he died twice in Fable: The Lost Chapters. It was easy to be good, evil, or neutral.  The weapon and armor selection was huge. Magic was strong.

Fable II

The story line was okay. They added female Heroes. They took away armor and replaced it with regular clothing. They also removed crossbows and replaced them with guns. Magic was still pretty much the same. The world was pretty cool. Very disappointed in the final boss. He was blabbing away, I took out my gun, shot him, and he died. And that was it.

Fable III

Started off a little rocky. They took away axes, cleavers, and maces. Now, you can only use swords and hammers for melee. Pistols and rifles for ranged. And they added spell gauntlets; meaning you can only use one spell at a time, and you have to keep going back to the sanctuary every time you want to use another spell. There's something called Spell Weaving. That lets you use two spells at a time. They kept some of the areas, like Bowerstone. The clothing they give you is pretty cool. Especially the outfit you get when you become king/queen, the armor set, and the mage set. Walter was the best character in the game. He trains you to become a Hero. He also dies at the end. The final boss, The Crawler, possesses Walter and you have to kill him, obviously. I was kinda disappointed. Although I used 6 or 7 potions, he really wasn't that hard.

I still think the first one was the best.
